Package com.okta.sdk.resource.client

Class PagedIterable<T>

java.lang.Object
com.okta.sdk.resource.client.PagedIterable<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of item in the collection (e.g., User)
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>
public class PagedIterable<T> extends Object implements Iterable<T>
A new lazy, paginated iterable. This class is a "recipe" for fetching paginated data. It does no work until the iterator() method is called (e.g., by a for-each loop). Each call to iterator() creates a new, independent PagedIterator instance, ensuring thread-safety and isolation of pagination state.
